WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.866
Diagnosis relies on a tiered approach.

00:00:02.866 --> 00:00:06.210
Endomyocardial biopsy remains the histological gold standard

00:00:06.210 --> 00:00:09.553
— Dallas criteria require lymphocytic infiltration and

00:00:09.553 --> 00:00:12.897
myocyte necrosis — though sensitivity is limited

00:00:12.897 --> 00:00:14.330
by sampling error.

00:00:14.330 --> 00:00:17.673
Cardiac MRI with Lake Louise Criteria is

00:00:17.673 --> 00:00:21.017
now the preferred non-invasive modality: T2-weighted imaging

00:00:21.017 --> 00:00:24.361
identifies myocardial edema; T1 mapping and extracellular

00:00:24.361 --> 00:00:27.704
volume fraction quantify inflammation; and late gadolinium

00:00:27.704 --> 00:00:31.048
enhancement in a non-ischemic distribution confirms myocardial

00:00:31.048 --> 00:00:31.526
injury.

00:00:31.526 --> 00:00:34.869
Biomarkers including troponin I or T, CRP,

00:00:34.869 --> 00:00:38.213
and BNP support diagnosis and risk stratification.

00:00:38.213 --> 00:00:41.556
ESC guidelines recommend CMR in all patients

00:00:41.556 --> 00:00:44.900
with suspected myocarditis when echocardiography is inconclusive.
